 For constructing a capital M with a vertical bar through its middle in LaTeX, you have several approaches:

1. Using `\ooalign` to overlay characters:
```latex
\newcommand{\Mbar}{%
    \ooalign{M\cr\hfil\rule[-.2ex]{0.4pt}{2.3ex}\hfil\cr}%
}
```

2. Using TikZ for more control:
```latex
\newcommand{\Mbar}{%
    \tikz[baseline=(M.base)]{
        \node[inner sep=0] (M) {M};
        \draw[] (M.center) -- ($(M.center)+(0,1ex)$);
    }%
}
```

3. Using the `\stackinset` command from the stackengine package:
```latex
\usepackage{stackengine}
\newcommand{\Mbar}{%
    \stackinset{c}{0pt}{c}{0pt}{\rule{0.4pt}{2.3ex}}{M}%
}
```

The TikZ approach offers the most flexibility for adjusting the position and length of the vertical bar. You could also adjust the thickness by changing the line width parameter.

